parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag inflator can cause the airbag to rupture, resulting in serious injury or death to the driver or passengers.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag does not deploy in the event of a crash
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag inflator ruptures
and the airbag does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to repair or replace defective parts can lead to continued safety risks and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealerships are unable to repair or replace defective parts
dealerships are unaware of recalls
dealerships do not have the necessary equipment to perform repairs
dealerships are unable to provide a loaner vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause extended brake pedal travel, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or has difficulty stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, stall, or enter "limp home" mode, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses acceleration
stalls
or enters "limp home" mode
the engine RPM increases or decreases unexpectedly
the vehicle makes a loud noise
the wrench light or check engine light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or fails to shift gears
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle makes a loud noise
the wrench light or check engine light appears on the dashboard.
